http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/news/No-change-in-celeb%E2%80%99s-security-say-cops/article13989362.ece

The Mumbai Police on Friday said there was no change in police protection provided to film personalities in the city. The denial comes after a section of the media reported that a police security of 40 film actors and directors in Mumbai had been downscaled or withdrawn altogether.“We conduct periodic reviews for security cover provided to people. Reports of any downscaling or enhancing of security cover of any person are false,” said Mumbai Police spokesperson DCP Dhananjay Kulkarni.The Mumbai Police’s official Twitter handle too, tweeted saying, “There is no downscaling of existing personal security provided to film personalities.” The tweet tagged media outlets that had tweeted reports of the downscaling of security.On Friday, media reports said the Mumbai Police had decided to withdraw the existing security cover provided to actors Shah Rukh Khan and Aamir Khan, which was provided to them in light of their comments about the issue of intolerance in the country.The same reports went on to say that security cover of several film directors was completely withdrawn, while the cover of some others was downgraded. Media reports had said security cover for 25 personalities had been reduced.